nce\": \"China's table tennis association said the \\\"chaos\\\" of fan groups had interfered with the team's training and competition.\", \"from\": 968, \"to\": 1088, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 968, \"end\": 973, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9443678498761674, \"rank\": 0.04494047033082905, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The Public Security ministry said another case centered around gymnasts being insulted on social media.\", \"from\": 1090, \"to\": 1193, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1094, \"end\": 1118, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ministry_of_Public_Security_(China)\", \"score\": 0.9999999994918198, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Public Security ministry\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q327333\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ministry_of_Public_Security_(China)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Ministry_of_Public_Security_(China)\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"At the weekend, the Chinese Gymnastics Association said athletes, coaches, and managers had been the targets of rumors and insults, negatively impacting the work, life, and family of relevant personnel.\", \"from\": 1195, \"to\": 1397, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1215, \"end\": 1222, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chinese_language\", \"score\": 0.8957502601084681, \"rank\": 0.11352122337392895, \"text\": \"Chinese\", \"types\": [\"Q315\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chinese_language\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chinese_language\"}, {\"begin\": 1223, \"end\": 1233, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gymnastics\", \"score\": 0.9991221083269249, \"rank\": 0.0008783461905936848, \"text\": \"Gymnastics\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gymnastics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Gymnastics\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The statements came after swimmer Pan Zhanle, 20, who broke the\\u00a0world record\\u00a0in the 100-meter freestyle, disbanded his only fan group page on social medial platform Weibo and told state broadcaster CCTV that he preferred to keep a low profile.\", \"from\": 1399, \"to\": 1642, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1564, \"end\": 1569, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sina_Weibo\", \"score\": 0.9999999972742444, \"rank\": 2.7085192062912266e-09, \"text\": \"Weibo\", \"types\": [\"Q386724\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sina_Weibo\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Sina_Weibo\"}, {\"begin\": 1597, \"end\": 1601, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_Central_Television\", \"score\": 0.9999997451318775, \"rank\": 2.5486824692272915e-07, \"text\": \"CCTV\", \"types\": [\"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\", \"Q15265344\", \"Q141683\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_Central_Television\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China_Central_Television\"}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"A bad thing about being famous is that too many people surround me,\\\" he said.\", \"from\": 1644, \"to\": 1722, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"I'd rather not have as much success if it meant I could continue training hard with peace of mind.\\\"\", \"from\": 1723, \"to\": 1823, \"entities\": []}, {\"sentence\": \"China delivered its\\u00a0best performance\\u00a0at a Summer Olympics since the 2008 Games on home soil, winning the joint most gold medals with the United States in Paris and only missing out on topping the standings on silver medal count.\", \"from\": 1825, \"to\": 2053, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1825, \"end\": 1830, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9443678498761674, \"rank\": 0.04494047033082905, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}, {\"begin\": 1962, \"end\": 1975, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/